HSH(1P)                  POSIX Programmer's Manual                 HSH(1P)


NAME
	hsh - shell, is a student project for a command language interpreter

SYNOPSIS
	hsh [-option]

DESCRIPTION
	The hsh is command language interpreter which reads from standard input and
	executes the commands and arguments passed.

OPTIONS
	There are no current options implemented.

EXAMPLES
	Interactive Mode:
		run the shell:
			./hsh
		write a command and arguments:
			command arguments

	Non Interactive Mode:
		pass the command through pipeline to the shell:
			echo "command arguments" | ./hsh

BUGS
	There are no known bugs.

FUTURE DIRECTIONS
	None.


